First timers! Did not know they serve dinner on Thursday and Friday only (3-8pm). Good thing we came on a Thursday night! We arrived right before the rush and were seated right away. The place is very small. It started to get super busy around 6/6:15 and there was a wait for other people. Staff was very friendly and helpful. Water was always filled. Food came out fast. Kids enjoyed typical kids menu items (chicken fingers and burger). The kids burger was huge. French fries delicious. Ordered one of the specials which was pot roast. Roast and gravy were delicious. Other items that came with were okay but nothing to write home about (matza ball soup, green beans, potato pancake). I ordered the patty melt. Classic diner menu item. Burger came out well done and dry. Not seasoned very well, had to load it up with mustard, mayo and ketchup. The potato salad was good. We came based on a recommendation and probably would come back to try the breakfast but it's located about half hour away from us and most likely won't make the drive again.
